Sidhant Ahluwalia

Co-Host

Sid is a graduate from U Rochester where he started a entrepreneurship club, was a senator, failed a class, struggled with getting jobs and also graduated with High Distinction. He hustled his way to Deloitte, Accenture and now is at TCS. Before founding this website that you are reading this in, he ran his professional consulting company where he helped 40+ students get closer to their dream (or any) job.

Sharfuz Shifat

Co-Host

Sharfuz is a U Rochester alum where he started a entrepreneurship club, failed a class, changed majors every weekend, struggled with getting jobs, drank too much coffee and had his life fall apart everyday on repeat. Somehow he managed to graduate with a High Distinction and was a software engineer intern at FedEx Services. He is currently working as an M&A Analyst at Hitachi. He also started a startup to help other people with their startups in college....(just ask him on our behalf)

Moss Rahman

UI UX & Brand lead

Moss is a senior at UNC Chapel Hill. He is passionate about everything to do with UI/UX, graphics, branding and advertising. He is a proud Tar Heel, makes a mean white Russian, loves driving his car and will run you over with his car if you move a single object in his room by an inch.

Aliye Gallagher

Digital Strategy Advisor

Aliye loves emails. So much so, that she created an entire degree all about email communications! Not really. Aliye graduated in 2019 with an interdepartmental (aka DIY) degree in Digital Communications: Theory, Analysis, Practice. She continued on to California, joining 16 others in the first cohort of Experience Lab at UC Berkeley. Aliye is a strong advocate for alternative educational paths, experiential learning (clearly) and making it up as you go along. She founded and runs a photo and video business for the past six years, which has now expanded into a digital strategy, web design and development, and many forms of digital art firm. Aliye has worked in London and Dublin, and is always looking around the corner for the next opportunity (her dad calls it the 'jedi mind trick').

Sekelile Mkhabela

Community & Outreach

Seke, a rising senior from the University of Rochester hails from the lovely Kingdom of eSwatini. She is a double major in International Relations and Economics with a minor in French. During her time at Rochester, she has studied abroad in Belgium, been an orientation leader, a tour guide, a student alumni ambassador and apart of Student Government.

Michelle Shuai

Editor & Writer

Michelle is a rising sophomore at U Rochester from Honolulu, Hawaii. She currently envisions herself as an Economics major, but because she also has many other interests, she re-thinks her academic plan very often. In her first year at UR, Michelle has been the deputy chair of a Student Government committee, a flutist in Wind Symphony, and an editor at the Campus Times. In her spare time, Michelle goes on hikes to make up for the excessive amounts of milk tea and boba she consumes.

Aman Shrestha

Front End Developer

Aman is a rising senior at the University of Rochester who prioritizes sleep over most things. Originally from Nepal, Aman has spent the last three years pursuing his degree in computer science. He has been actively involved in the CS community at the university and has led organizing the university’s annual hackathon twice and now is leading the CS Undergraduate council. Other priorities of Aman include food, specially mo:mo which is a special nepali dumpling that is his second priority,right before sleep.

Maggie Peng

Video Editor

Maggie Peng is a recent graduate from the University of Rochester where she double majored in Anthropology and Psychology. She is passionate about videography, graphic design, and marketing. When she is editing videos, she is too in the zone to hear anything besides what is going on in her Final Cut Pro. During her time at U of R, she was working as a marketing specialist at the Barbara J. Burger iZone where she has helped establish it’s brand and online video presence.

Daniel Munoz

Podcast Host

Daniel is a Computer Science major at the University of Rochester graduating in 2021. At the university he is the president of the Society of Hispanic Professional Engineers (SHPE) club as well as a tutor. He was born and raised in Mexico, the cards that life dealt him led him to only be raised by his grandparents from a very young age. However, resilience and a growth mindset have aided him in conquering the challenges that life throws around and develop a mindset to succeed in the face of adversity. He’s been involved with a student led startup since his first year, research with the medical center, and has interned as a Software Engineer for Autodesk. In his free time he enjoys to go on long bike rides and listen to audiobooks or practice different forms of dancing such as shuffling, electroswing or breakdancing!

William Anderson

Chief Mascot Officer

Unlike the rest of us Will is just here for the show. He came with the website and we can't figure out how to get rid of him...but we think he is someone who will became an APM at Google upon graduation, after being a summer intern at McKinsey, which he did the summer after he sold his company for Millions, a company that was inspired by his freshman year software engineering internship at Facebook. What do you think?
